The paper discusses optimizations for a web archiving service, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques such as federated search and caching. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The use of machine learning models for predicting archival holdings suggests a connection to sub-categories such as cs.DL (digital libraries) and cs.DB (databases). The focus on improving response times for human-driven services suggests a connection to cs.HC (human-computer interaction). Finally, the use of machine learning models also suggests a connection to cs.AI (artificial intelligence).
